## 5. Federal Tax Lien vs. Levy Flowchart

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph Lien["FEDERAL TAX LIEN"]
        LienDef[LIEN = Legal CLAIM<br/>Against ALL Property]
        LienDef --> LienArise[Arises Automatically When:<br/>1. Assessment Made<br/>2. Notice and Demand Sent<br/>3. Taxpayer Fails to Pay]
        LienArise --> LienEffect[Effects:<br/>- Attaches to all property<br/>- Protects government priority<br/>- Can affect credit score]
        LienEffect --> NFTL[Notice of Federal Tax Lien<br/>Form 668Y<br/>Filed with County/State]
        NFTL --> LienPublic[Makes Lien PUBLIC<br/>- Credit bureaus notified<br/>- Other creditors on notice]
    end

    subgraph Levy["LEVY"]
        LevyDef[LEVY = Actual SEIZURE<br/>of Specific Property]
        LevyDef --> LevyReq[Requirements Before Levy:<br/>1. Tax assessed and unpaid<br/>2. Notice and demand sent<br/>3. 30-day Final Notice<br/>4. CDP rights provided]
        LevyReq --> LevyAction[Levy Actions:<br/>- Garnish wages<br/>- Seize bank accounts<br/>- Take property]
    end

    subgraph Compare["COMPARISON"]
        Comparison{Key<br/>Difference}
        Comparison -->|Lien| Passive[PASSIVE<br/>Secures debt<br/>Does not take property]
        Comparison -->|Levy| Active[ACTIVE<br/>Actually takes<br/>property/money]
    end

    subgraph Release["RELEASE/WITHDRAWAL"]
        LienRelease[Lien Released When:<br/>- Debt paid in full<br/>- Bond accepted<br/>- 10-year CSED expires<br/>- Accepted OIC]
        LevyRelease[Levy Released When:<br/>- Debt satisfied<br/>- Installment agreement<br/>- Hardship shown<br/>- CSED expires]
    end

    subgraph Exempt["PROPERTY EXEMPT FROM LEVY"]
        ExemptList[Cannot Levy:<br/>- Necessary clothing/schoolbooks<br/>- Furniture up to $9,840<br/>- Tools of trade up to $4,920<br/>- Unemployment benefits<br/>- Workers compensation<br/>- Child support payments<br/>- Minimum exempt wages<br/>- Principal residence*]
        ExemptList --> ResNote[*Principal residence requires<br/>court approval and<br/>written approval from<br/>IRS District Director]
    end
```

### Lien vs. Levy Comparison Table

| Aspect | Federal Tax Lien | Levy |
|--------|------------------|------|
| **What it is** | Legal claim against property | Actual seizure of property |
| **When it arises** | Automatic: assessment + notice + non-payment | Requires 30-day final notice |
| **Effect** | Secures government interest | Takes property/wages/bank funds |
| **Public notice** | NFTL filed with county/state | N/A |
| **Credit impact** | Yes, after NFTL filed | N/A directly |
| **Property affected** | All property (current & future) | Specific property seized |
| **Release** | Full payment, bond, CSED expires, OIC | Payment, hardship, IA, CSED expires |

